yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Point-Clouds-3D-Perception-with-Open3D
yudhisteer.description: Using the KITTI dataset, we employed Open3D to visualize, downsample, segment with RANSAC, cluster via DBSCAN, create 3D bounding boxes, and perform surface reconstruction on point clouds.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/UAV-Drone-Object-Tracking-using-Kalman-Filter
yudhisteer.description: This project proposes the implementation of a Linear Kalman Filter from scratch to track stationary objects and individuals or animals approaching a drone's landing position, aiming to mitigate collision risks.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/3D-Reconstruction-with-Uncalibrated-Stereo
yudhisteer.description: The project explores 3D reconstruction using Multi-View Stereo (MVS) and Structure from Motion (SfM). We show the equations how to calibrate an uncalibrated stereo then reproject our image to 3D space.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Reinforcement-Learning-for-Supply-Chain-Management
yudhisteer.description: The goal of the project was to design the logistic model of autonomous robots that would supply garment parts from the Cutting Dept to the Makeup Dept in the shortest time possible and using the most optimized path.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Augmented-Reality-and-IoT-for-Machines-Monitoring
yudhisteer.description: The second phase of the AR project for predictive maintenance is to combine IoT and AR to get a real-time visualization of the status of machines in the production plants.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Optical-Flow-Obstacle-Avoidance-for-UAV
yudhisteer.description: In this project I aim to develop an unsupervised sense-and-avoid system for UAVs using sparse and dense optical flow.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Robotic-Grasping-Detection-with-PointNet
yudhisteer.description: This project focuses on training robots to grasp everyday objects accurately. We gather a unique point cloud dataset using an iPhone's LiDAR and process it with Polycam. We develop a PointNet model from scratch to perform multi-class classification and part-segmentation, guiding the robot on where to grasp objects.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Augmented-Reality-for-Preventive-Maintenance
yudhisteer.description: For the first phase of the AR project, the goal was to show how AR could be used in preventive maintenance and in the training of maintenance crews.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Face-Recognition-with-Masks
yudhisteer.description: This project involves automating the attendance system of RT Knits using Face Recognition. Due to Covid-19, people are obliged to wear masks hence, the system is successful in recognizing people despite wearing masks.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Digital-Twin-of-Anthropomorphic-Robotic-Arm
yudhisteer.description: This project consists of research on a 6 degree of freedom robot. A 3D model of the robot has been made on Unity to demonstrate Forward and Inverse Kinematics. Important concepts in robotics like Singularities, Path planning and Motion Control are explained as well.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Generating-Design-Ideas-from-Keywords
yudhisteer.description: The purpose of the project is to understand a basic GAN from scratch. A WGAN was built to generate people's faces based in the Celeba Dataset.  VQGAN + CLIP model was used to generate unique designs that would be used in fashion.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Real-time-Multi-Object-Tracking-for-Rescue-Operations
yudhisteer.description: This project shows the implementation of tracking algorithms like SORT and Deep SORT from scratch.  The project aims to assist emergency responders in assessing the number of people at a disaster site and tracking their movements for rescue operations, especially in situations where they are being carried away by floodwaters.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Learning-3D-Vision-with-Inverse-Graphics---Part-I
yudhisteer.description: This project shows the basic of 3D vision which involves mesh, point cloud and voxel grid. The first part is about transforming 2D data into 3D.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Vision-Transformer-Based-Multi-Class-Classification-for-Simulated-6DoF-Robot
yudhisteer.description: The project shows how to create our own large-scale synthetic dataset for multi-class classification. The goal is to create a Vision Transformer model from scratch and run it in a digital twin made in Unity with a 6 DoF robot for palletization process.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Lane-Detection-with-Semantic-Segmentation
yudhisteer.description: Lane detection using Semantic Segmentation. To be used in industries by autonomous shuttles in a controlled environment.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Predicting-the-Price-of--Anything--on-Stock-Market-Vol.1
yudhisteer.description: This project is about beating the market and debugging a myth: LSTM + Stock Market = $$$.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Box-Optimization-with-Genetic-Algorithm
yudhisteer.description: The goal of this project is to select an optimized container dimensions to load products that will reduce space wastage. By optimzing the total volume occupied by the products and their total weights, we seek the best orientation and position of the products during loading.

yudhisteer.name: yudhisteer/Phase-2_Automating-QC-with-Detectron2
yudhisteer.description: The second phase of the project is to automate the process of taking garment measurements and data entry using Computer Vision.

yudhisteer.description: Understanding CI/CD pipeline with python packaging.

yudhisteer.description: Load, clean, and visualize scraped Google Play Store data to gain insights into the Android app market.

yudhisteer.description: This repositiory is about exploring fun datasets to extract insights and be able to adopt meaningful data visualization for storytelling.

yudhisteer.description: This project consisted of automating the process of taking measurements of garments in the Quality Control Department.

yesoun.description: Using LIBLAS we find the estimate positions of vehicle from Aerial LIDAR scans mounted on a Drone flying over the top of the road. The idea is not based on 3D CNNs, but it is rather based on trimming the 3D search space by excluding any set of point cloud that does not belong to the road, then downsampling of PC using 3D Voxelization and move a 3D fix-sized box (at the beginning) and search the ones that have the highest occupancy.

yesoun.name: yesoun/PCAP_WIRESHARK_JSON_PCAP_C-
yesoun.description: Program will read the pcap file, parsing the main file header, and each packet header. See https://wiki.wireshark.org/Development/LibpcapFileFormat for a discussion of the PCAP file format. Program will write out a JSON  format file. Including the following fields (indexed with the specified strings)  "magicNumber" -- PCAP magic number "majorVersion"   -- PCAP file major version number "minorVersion" -- PCAP minor version number "thisZone" -- PCAP time zone (GMT to local correction) "sigFigs" -- accuracy of timestamps "snapLen" -- maximum packet size "network" -- data link type "count" -- total number of packets read in this file. Your program will have to calculate this and for each packet   a packet number, starting at 0 (See posted format) "tmSec" -- timestamp seconds "tmUSec" -- timestamp microseconds "inclLen" -- number of octets/bytes of packet in the pcap file "origLen" -- number of octets/byets of packet on the network (will be same as inclLen unless bigger than snapLen  Sample output format: (newlines don't matter here. Also, order of fields in {...}  don't matter.

ynyeh0221.name: ynyeh0221/fashion-mnist-generative-diffusion
ynyeh0221.description: A PyTorch implementation of a diffusion model for generating Fashion-MNIST-like digit images. The repository demonstrates both unconditional and conditional image generation, clearly showing how diffusion models remove noise step-by-step to generate digits from random noise or from a numeric prompt.

ynyeh0221.name: ynyeh0221/Oxford-102-Flower-GAN-VAE-latent-diffusion
ynyeh0221.description: A class-conditional image generation framework that combines a Variational Autoencoder (VAE) and a Denoising Diffusion Probabilistic Model (DDPM), tailored for the Oxford 102 Flowers dataset. The architecture features channel/spatial attention, center loss regularization, perceptual VGG loss, and GAN-based refinement.

ynyeh0221.name: ynyeh0221/model-insight-rag
ynyeh0221.description: A modular agentic Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system for managing AI model scripts, metadata, and generated images. Supports advanced querying, schema-based validation, image search, model comparison, and Colab notebook generation. Powered by Chroma, LangChain, BGE-M3, OpenCLIP, Deepseek, Streamlit, and a custom Schema Registry.

ynyeh0221.name: ynyeh0221/vecraft-vector-database
ynyeh0221.description: VecraftDB is an embeddable Python vector database with MVCC transactions, WAL durability, HNSW similarity search, JSON/metadata filtering, mmap+SQLite storage, Prometheus metrics, and a FastAPI server. Snapshot‑safe, crash‑proof, one‑command startup—ideal for AI apps and edge deployments. Handles async CRUD, search + t‑SNE without blocking writers.

ynyeh0221.name: ynyeh0221/mnist-generative-diffusion
ynyeh0221.description: A PyTorch implementation of a diffusion model for generating MNIST-like digit images. The repository demonstrates both unconditional and conditional image generation, clearly showing how diffusion models remove noise step-by-step to generate digits from random noise or from a numeric prompt.

ynyeh0221.name: ynyeh0221/CIFAR10-cat-dog-generative-image-diffusion
ynyeh0221.description: A PyTorch implementation of a diffusion model for generating CIFAR10 (cat/dog)-like digit images. The repository demonstrates both unconditional and conditional image generation, clearly showing how diffusion models remove noise step-by-step to generate digits from random noise or from a numeric prompt.

ynyeh0221.name: ynyeh0221/seq2seq-math-models
ynyeh0221.description: A collection of Transformer and RNN-based Seq2Seq models for arithmetic operations (addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division). Includes scripts, training data generation, and evaluation tools to showcase model performance and facilitate further experimentation.

ynyeh0221.name: ynyeh0221/conditional-cat-dog-generative-latent-diffusion
ynyeh0221.description: A PyTorch implementation of a latent diffusion model for generating cat/dog-like digit images. The repository demonstrates both unconditional and conditional image generation, clearly showing how diffusion models remove noise step-by-step to generate digits from random noise or from a numeric prompt.

ynyeh0221.name: ynyeh0221/celebA-generative-latent-diffusion-model
ynyeh0221.description: Advanced generative model combining VAE-GAN and conditional diffusion to create high-quality CelebA face images based on the "Smiling" attribute. Features state-of-the-art architectures with attention mechanisms, perceptual losses, and extensive visualizations of the generative process and latent space dynamics.
